The paper discusses a novel multi-scale architecture for graph-structured time series modeling, which involves learning complex features from spatio-temporal structures. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given the focus on deep learning and structured data, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI.
